    <h2>How to Build Your First Hedge: Step-by-Step Guide</h2>

    <div class="step">
        <h3><span class="step-num">1</span> Assess Your Current Exposure</h3>
        <p>Calculate the total dollar value of your meme coin portfolio. Include all wallets, all chains, and all positions. This is your "exposure number." For this example, let's say $25,000 total across 5 meme coins on Solana.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
        <h3><span class="step-num">2</span> Choose Your Hedge Percentage</h3>
        <p>Based on current market conditions. June 2026: BTC is testing $66K support, meme coins have been volatile but resilient. Recommended: 35% hedge ratio. You want to protect $8,750 of your $25,000.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
        <h3><span class="step-num">3</span> Select Your Hedge Instrument</h3>
        <p>SOL-PERP short on Hyperliquid is the best choice. The correlation between SOL and Solana meme coins is 0.7-0.82. You need ~$9,500 notional in SOL short to achieve $8,750 effective protection (accounting for imperfect correlation).</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
        <h3><span class="step-num">4</span> Set Up the Position</h3>
        <p>Deposit USDC to Hyperliquid. Open a short position on SOL-PERP for the calculated size. Use 2-3x leverage to minimize capital requirements. Set a stop loss on the short in case SOL rallies (you don't want to get margin called).</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
        <h3><span class="step-num">5</span> Monitor and Rebalance</h3>
        <p>Check your hedge every 24-48 hours. Adjust the ratio if correlations change. Roll the perpetual position as needed (every 7-8 days to avoid excessive funding costs). If BTC breaks above $68K resistance, reduce the hedge to 20%.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
        <h3><span class="step-num">6</span> Exit When Appropriate</h3>
        <p>The goal is not to hold the hedge forever. Exit when: (a) BTC reclaims a key support level, (b) the macroeconomic outlook improves, (c) your meme coins are in strong uptrends, or (d) you've identified an even better entry point to re-deploy capital.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>Common Hedging Mistakes (And How to Avoid Them)</h2>

    <div class="warning-box">
        <strong>�Œ Mistake #1: Over-Hedging</strong><br>
        Protecting 100% of your portfolio removes ALL upside. If BTC pumps 20% and you're fully hedged, your meme coins gain 30% but your short loses 20% ” net return: 10% instead of 30%. You paid the price of insurance without needing it.<br><br>
        <strong>�… Fix:</strong> Never hedge more than 70-80% of your portfolio. Leave room for upside.
    </div>

    <div class="warning-box">
        <strong>�Œ Mistake #2: Hedging the Wrong Asset</strong><br>
        If you own $BONK but hedge with ETH-PERP, the correlation is too weak (0.3-0.4). When memes crash 30%, ETH might only drop 8%. Your hedge barely helps.<br><br>
        <strong>�… Fix:</strong> Match your hedge to your holdings. Solana memes �™ SOL or BTC. Ethereum memes �™ ETH or BTC.
    </div>

    <div class="warning-box">
        <strong>�Œ Mistake #3: Ignoring Funding Costs</strong><br>
        Perpetual futures have funding rates. In bull markets, funding is positive (longs pay shorts). Your short position earns money. In bear markets, funding can flip negative ” you pay to stay short. Over a month, this can add up to 5-15% of your position size.<br><br>
        <strong>�… Fix:</strong> Check funding rates daily. On Coinglass or Velo. If funding turns too negative, close the perpetual and switch to puts or stablecoins.
    </div>

    <div class="warning-box">
        <strong>�Œ Mistake #4: Hedging Too Late</strong><br>
        The worst time to hedge is AFTER a crash has started. By then, your meme coins are already down 40%, and the perpetual short carries gap risk (slippage when entering during panic).<br><br>
        <strong>�… Fix:</strong> Set conditional triggers ahead of time. "If BTC drops below $65K, I hedge 40%." Automate this with a stop-loss order or a trading bot.
    </div>

    <div class="warning-box">
        <strong>�Œ Mistake #5: Tax Blindness</strong><br>
        Hedging creates taxable events. Every time you rotate to stablecoins, short a perpetual, or close a position, you may trigger a capital gain or loss. In the US, crypto-to-crypto trades are taxable events.<br><br>
        <strong>�… Fix:</strong> Use tools like CoinTracker or Koinly. Consider tax-loss harvesting alongside your hedging strategy. Read the <a href="/crypto-tax-loss-harvesting-solana-offset-gains-smart-timing-2026">DogeKing crypto tax-loss harvesting guide</a> for details.
    </div>

